#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.57:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Sūkarakhatavagga"
msgstr "6. The Boar’s Cave"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 57. Sahampatibrahmasutta → brahmasuttaṃ (bj) | brahmā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Sahampatibrahmasutta"
msgstr "57. With Brahmā Sahampati"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.57:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhe paṭhamābhisambuddho."
msgstr ""
"At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā "
"at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.3"
msgid ""
"“pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni bahulīkatāni amatogadhāni honti amataparāyaṇāni "
"amatapariyosānāni."
msgstr ""
"“When these five faculties are developed and cultivated they culminate, "
"finish, and end in the deathless."

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.4"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.5"
msgid ""
"Saddhindriyaṃ bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ amatogadhaṃ hoti amataparāyaṇaṃ "
"amatapariyosānaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of faith,"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.6"
msgid "Vīriyindriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "energy,"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.7"
msgid "satindriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "mindfulness,"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.8"
msgid "samādhindriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "immersion,"

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.9"
msgid ""
"paññindriyaṃ bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ amatogadhaṃ hoti amataparāyaṇaṃ "
"amatapariyosānaṃ."
msgstr "and wisdom."

msgctxt "sn48.57:1.10"
msgid ""
"Imāni pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni bahulīkatāni amatogadhāni honti "
"amataparāyaṇāni amatapariyosānānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When these five faculties are developed and cultivated they culminate, "
"finish, and end in the deathless.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.57:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi "
"nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ "
"samiñjeyya; evameva brahmaloke antarahito bhagavato purato pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmā Sahampati knew what the Buddha was thinking. As easily as a "
"strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the "
"Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā "
"tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the "
"Buddha, and said:"

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.3"
msgid "“evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ sugata."
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!"

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.4"
msgid ""
"Pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni bahulīkatāni amatogadhāni honti amataparāyaṇāni "
"amatapariyosānāni."
msgstr ""
"When these five faculties are developed and cultivated they culminate, "
"finish, and end in the deathless."

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.5"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.6"
msgid ""
"Saddhindriyaṃ bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ amatogadhaṃ hoti amataparāyaṇaṃ "
"amatapariyosānaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ amatogadhaṃ hoti "
"amataparāyaṇaṃ amatapariyosānaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom."

msgctxt "sn48.57:2.7"
msgid ""
"Imāni pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni bahulīkatāni amatogadhāni honti "
"amataparāyaṇāni amatapariyosānāni."
msgstr ""
"When these five faculties are developed and cultivated they culminate, "
"finish, and end in the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.57:3.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, bhante, kassape sammāsambuddhe brahmacariyaṃ acariṃ."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, sir, I lived the spiritual life under the fully awakened "
"Buddha Kassapa."

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.2"
msgid "Tatrapi maṃ evaṃ jānanti:"
msgstr "There they knew me as"

# This curious detail seems to imply that names continue across lives …
msgctxt "sn48.57:3.3"
msgid "‘sahako bhikkhu, sahako bhikkhū’ti."
msgstr "the mendicant Sahaka."

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.4"
msgid ""
"So khvāhaṃ, bhante, imesaṃyeva pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ brahmalokaṃ "
"upapanno."
msgstr ""
"Because of developing and cultivating these same five faculties I lost "
"desire for sensual pleasures. When my body broke up, after death, I was "
"reborn in a good place, in the Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.5"
msgid "Tatrapi maṃ evaṃ jānanti:"
msgstr "There they know me as"

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.6"
msgid "‘brahmā sahampati, brahmā sahampatī’ti."
msgstr "Brahmā Sahampati."

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.7"
msgid "Evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ sugata."
msgstr "That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!"

msgctxt "sn48.57:3.8"
msgid ""
"Ahametaṃ jānāmi, ahametaṃ passāmi yathā imāni pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni "
"bahulīkatāni amatogadhāni honti amataparāyaṇāni amatapariyosānānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"I know and see how when these five faculties are developed and cultivated "
"they culminate, finish, and end in the deathless.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.57:3.9"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
